  "title": "Full Stack Developer (Central Area )",
  "description": "<p></p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The Full Stack Engineer will design, develop, deploy, and maintain scalable, high-performance, and secure web applications. You will leverage expertise in frontend and backend development, cloud technologies, DevOps automation, and application security within an Agile, DevOps-driven environment to ensure software quality, security, and maintainability.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design and implement scalable and secure frontend web applications using at least two technologies such as Javascript, Typescript, React, Next, Vue, Angular, or Svelte to deliver high-quality user experiences</li><li>Develop and maintain backend services and APIs using at least two technologies such as Nodejs, Expressjs, Nestjs, ROR, Java, or Restful APIs to ensure robust and efficient server-side functionality</li><li>Deploy and manage applications on cloud platforms to optimize performance, scalability, and availability</li><li>Automate DevOps processes to streamline continuous integration and continuous delivery pipelines, enhancing deployment speed and reliability</li><li>Collaborate within Agile teams to deliver iterative software improvements while maintaining high standards of code quality, security, and maintainability</li><li>Implement application security best practices to protect data integrity and user privacy throughout the software lifecycle</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Work schedule: 5-day week</li><li>Location: Central area</li></ul><p><br /><br />Maestro HR</p><p>damien lee tian hong</p><p>R1106726</p><p>16C8462</p>",
